The Dow Jones industrial average broke above 25,000 for the first time ever on Thursday, tying the fastest 1,000-point move in its history. This milestone was achieved following the release of stronger-than-expected jobs data. According to Steve Claussen, vice president of trader strategy at ETRADE, the Dow hitting 25,000 was a significant achievement and symbolically important. He also highlighted the underlying strength that is driving the markets to such high levels. The article also mentions that equities are off to a strong start in 2018, with the Nasdaq completing its best two-day start to a year since 2006.